################ Rules ###############
Watch Key levels -> Support, Resistance, Previous day High/Low, 52 week High/Low, Any News
Wait First 10–15 Minutes After Market Open -> Don't decide immediately
Do not take too many lots in one trade. -> Stop averaging too much
Maintain Trading Journal -> Entry reason, Exit reason, Mistakes
Don’t Average Losing Trades
Don’t Trade Without Stop Loss
Don’t Buy Far OTM Options
Don’t Trade During News (RBI policy, Budget, Global news etc.) Without Plan.
Don’t Overtrade -> 1–3 quality trades per day.
Don’t Hold Losing Options Hoping for Recovery.
Maximum time avoid buying Nifty, Bank Nifty if you're unsure.
Prefer Hedging with low quantity (max 3 qty)

⭐ Golden Rules Professional Traders Follow

1️. Capital protection first -> Maximum loss per trade = ₹5,000–₹10,000
2️. Cut loss quickly
3️. Let profits run
4️. Trade with trend
5️. Small position sizes

📊 Simple Strategy Many NIFTY Traders Use
For **NIFTY 50 intraday options:

Break Resistance → Buy CE
Break Support → Buy PE

Stop loss: 20–25% premium

Target:40–60% premium

Risk-reward should be 1:2 minimum.

############## Buy ######################

Always decide risk before entering (Strict Stoploss)
Take only 1 qty while starting
Average when it goes beyond the price (25%) and observe support, resistance level
Maximum take 3 qty, do not average more.

############# Sell #######################

Don't be greedy, book the profit when it seen
Focus on market volatility
Once booked, don't buy same share


############ Hedging ##################
If you take many lots, hedge immediately.

Always Hedge when you've Large Positions
Use Opposite Option Hedge
| Position | Hedge        |
| -------- | ------------ |
| Buy CE   | Buy small PE |
| Buy PE   | Buy small CE |



